    <text type="note" xml:lang="ru" xml:id="letter-09087"> 
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date when-custom="1788-09-18">1788 г. сентября 18.</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>К <persName ref="people.xml#ero01">Еропкину</persName> написать надлежит, чтоб <rs ref="people.xml#ero01">он</rs> <rs ref="people.xml#wac01 people.xml#wac02">графов Вахмейстеров обоих</rs> послал жить в <placeName ref="places.xml#kal01">Калугу</placeName>, о чем и дать знать <persName ref="people.xml#kre01">Кречетникову</persName>, чтоб <rs ref="people.xml#kre01">он</rs> <rs ref="people.xml#wac01 people.xml#wac02">их</rs> <rs ref="places.xml#kal01">там</rs> поместил, и приличной имел за <rs ref="people.xml#wac01 people.xml#wac02">ними</rs> присмотр.
                <note type="editorial">
                    <persName ref="people.xml#wac01">Claes Adam Wachtmeister</persName> and his brother  <persName ref="people.xml#wac02">Hans Friedrich Wachtmeister</persName> who commanded the ship <title>"Prince Gustav"</title>and all his crew were captured during the <name type="event" ref="events.xml#hogla01">battle of Hogland</name>. They were first sent to <placeName ref="places.xml#mos01">Moscow</placeName> and then, as their presence there provoked too much interest, to <placeName ref="places.xml#kal01">Kaluga</placeName> (
                    <bibl> 
                        <title ref="works.xml#dnevni01">Dnevnik A.V. Khrapovitskago 1782-1793</title>
                        , <biblScope unit="pp">pp. 104, 156, 461.</biblScope>
                    </bibl>
                    ).
                </note>
            </p>
        </body>
